OL,6,FHe said: "When Aliza arrived in the
OL,7,Fhospital, she was, for use of a better
OL,8,Fword, broken in half ` her top half
OL,9,Fwasn't connected to the bottom half.
OL,11,F"I was concerned that the damage had
OL,12,Falready been done, and my first
OL,13,Fthought was that this girl might never
OL,14,Fwalk again."
OL,16,FAliza's mother Thirza AliKhan, from
OL,17,FDorset, said: "It was a long day, a
OL,18,Fday I will never forget. We didn't
OL,19,Fknow what was going to happen and I
OL,20,Fsuppose it didn't really hit us until
OL,21,Fthe next morning.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/8
