OL,4,Cbeing 'broken in half' from horse fall
OL,6,FMr Davies explained: "This was a more
OL,7,Fcomplex procedure, as we had to access
OL,8,Fthe spine through her chest and
OL,9,Fabdomen to remove the damaged
OL,10,Fvertebrae and insert screws into her
OL,11,Fbone.
OL,13,F"The vertebrae were then replaced with
OL,14,Fan expanding cage, to hold the spine
OL,15,Fin place while it healed.
OL,17,F"The surgery was a success, but we had
OL,18,Fno idea if this would mean Aliza Rae
OL,19,Fwould ever walk again."
